  "text": "Array comparative genomic hybridization. The human BAC arrays were purchased from the University of California at San Francisco Array Core. Each array consists of 2,464 BAC clones spotted in triplicate on chromium slides [CITATION_1] . The resolution is ∼1.4 Mb. The imaging set up and custom software are described elsewhere (6). We followed our published hybridization protocol (5), but with a 72-h hybridization. Imaging processing was done with the University of California at San Francisco SPOT version 2.1 and SPROC version 2.0 software packages [CITATION_2] .",
